WEBVTT

00:02.127 --> 00:04.545
NARRATOR: Previously on Terminator:
The Sarah Connor Chronicles:

00:04.713 --> 00:08.716
I'm here because Sarah Connor is a
deluded, dangerous whack-a-mole...

00:08.884 --> 00:10.927
...who killed a man
because she believes...

00:11.095 --> 00:14.472
...he'll invent a computer system
that declares war on the world.

00:14.640 --> 00:17.600
I'm looking for this girl.
Have you seen my niece?

00:17.768 --> 00:19.560
There was a guy here
looking for your sister.

00:19.728 --> 00:21.396
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

00:21.563 --> 00:23.648
-I'll get rid of him.
-Riley.

00:24.024 --> 00:27.568
-lf you don't leave, I'm calling the police.
JOHN: That guy's really dangerous.

00:27.736 --> 00:28.778
Really dangerous.

00:28.946 --> 00:31.364
This has nothing to do with Riley.
You're pissed.

00:31.532 --> 00:35.576
I found someone I actually
like spending time with, and it's not you.

00:39.998 --> 00:42.458
[POUNDING]

00:46.171 --> 00:50.258
JOHN: Riley, look at me.
RILEY: Show me that. That's horrifying.

00:50.426 --> 00:53.553
JOHN: It's supposed to stop cars
from playing Ping-Pong with your head.

00:53.721 --> 00:57.140
RILEY: Hey, I think your mom's out here.
Hi, Mrs. Baum.

00:57.307 --> 00:59.600
Thanks so much for having me over.

01:04.106 --> 01:06.816
JOHN: I didn't know if you were busy tonight
when I texted you.

01:07.151 --> 01:09.235
RILEY:
I'm never busy.

01:10.696 --> 01:12.155
I should do it again sometime?

01:12.531 --> 01:16.576
RILEY: Or maybe you could even call.
You know, with your voice.

01:16.744 --> 01:19.912
JOHN: Maybe I should try that sometime.
-Maybe you should.

01:21.373 --> 01:25.418
-See you soon?
-Okay. Be safe.

01:34.845 --> 01:36.596
I bought her a helmet.

01:38.265 --> 01:41.559
Responsible.
You think it'll stop a bullet?

01:42.269 --> 01:44.187
Why, are you gonna
take a shot at her?

01:45.397 --> 01:48.524
Well, a lot of bullets fly around here.
Someone will.

01:52.488 --> 01:53.863
You care about this girl?

01:56.241 --> 01:59.827
-Yeah.
-Then leave her alone.

02:09.922 --> 02:11.923
I'll talk to John.

02:12.841 --> 02:14.342
John's not listening.

02:15.093 --> 02:16.844
He's always listening.

02:37.658 --> 02:39.367
I was going to suggest a safe.

02:39.535 --> 02:43.246
Well, you might have suggested it
before we got robbed.

02:47.042 --> 02:48.626
SARAH:
Where are you going?

02:48.794 --> 02:52.547
I need to restock the supply drop.
We've been using a lot of ammunition.

02:53.382 --> 02:55.967
Business has been booming.
Where's John?

02:57.094 --> 02:59.679
-Still in his room.
-He hasn't gotten up yet?

02:59.847 --> 03:01.722
He needs more sleep than you do.

03:01.890 --> 03:05.351
It's because the circadian rhythm
of teenagers is abnormal.

03:06.061 --> 03:07.979
How late were you up talking to him?

03:08.230 --> 03:11.482
Not late.
He won't be seeing Riley anymore.

03:11.859 --> 03:14.443
-Is that so?
-John's not stupid.

03:16.989 --> 03:19.198
I don't like the way
he responds to you.

03:21.285 --> 03:23.327
You got what you wanted.

03:25.664 --> 03:27.582
[DRILL BUZZING]

04:10.667 --> 04:14.211
-Where is he?
-Check under the bed.

04:16.006 --> 04:18.090
You don't know.

04:23.263 --> 04:26.641
JOHN: I didn't know if you were busy
when I texted you tonight.

04:26.808 --> 04:28.434
RILEY:
I'm never busy.

04:30.479 --> 04:32.855
So then I guess
I should do it again sometime.

04:33.023 --> 04:35.691
Or maybe you could even call,
you know, with your voice.

04:36.276 --> 04:39.528
JOHN: Maybe I could try that.
-Maybe you should.

04:40.614 --> 04:44.033
-See you soon.
-Okay. Be safe.

04:57.214 --> 04:59.090
I'll talk to John.

04:59.257 --> 05:01.384
John's not listening.

05:01.677 --> 05:03.761
He's always listening.

05:22.114 --> 05:24.991
-Are you busy?
-No.

05:33.375 --> 05:37.336
-Did you change?
-It's hot out.

05:39.881 --> 05:42.216
Since when do you feel heat?

05:43.051 --> 05:44.885
I feel heat.

05:52.602 --> 05:54.770
Are you hoping
Riley's gonna see us in bed...

05:54.938 --> 05:57.940
...and be totally scarred
for the rest of her life?

05:58.108 --> 05:59.692
No.

05:59.860 --> 06:03.279
I watched Riley leave
till I couldn't see her anymore.

06:03.655 --> 06:06.115
And then you and Mom high-fived.

06:08.910 --> 06:11.412
You bring danger into Riley's life.

06:12.539 --> 06:14.415
I know that.

06:15.042 --> 06:16.125
I'm not stupid.

06:16.752 --> 06:19.628
But sometimes you do stupid things.

06:20.547 --> 06:23.174
It would help me to understand why.

06:25.302 --> 06:27.803
Humans do stupid things.

06:27.971 --> 06:31.015
So don't worry about it,
and be happy you're a machine.

06:31.558 --> 06:35.686
I'm a machine. I can't be happy.

06:37.939 --> 06:40.357
But I understand more than you think.

06:42.444 --> 06:44.612
You understand
I'm gonna keep seeing Riley...

06:44.780 --> 06:46.822
...even if everyone
thinks it's a bad idea?

06:47.282 --> 06:50.117
I understand that it's a bad idea.

06:50.869 --> 06:52.453
And...

06:53.205 --> 06:56.665
...I understand
that being John Connor can be lonely.

06:59.377 --> 07:02.755
Oh, yeah?
How do you understand that?

07:04.424 --> 07:06.550
You and I talk about it a lot.

07:08.470 --> 07:11.722
-We do?
-We do.

07:12.390 --> 07:14.100
We will.

07:22.901 --> 07:25.611
I need to get some sleep.

07:31.993 --> 07:33.744
And Riley?

07:35.163 --> 07:40.835
I know.

07:48.802 --> 07:52.930
-He won't be seeing Riley anymore.
-I don't like the way he responds to you.

07:54.015 --> 07:56.183
You got what you wanted.

08:27.757 --> 08:29.466
It's just you.

08:34.890 --> 08:38.225
-You been stealing my supplies?
-We needed to make a small bomb.

08:38.393 --> 08:41.520
I set this drop up with my people
for my people.

08:42.189 --> 08:46.108
-And everything's in here for a reason.
-John was supposed to ask.

08:49.237 --> 08:51.739
John needs to get his head
in the game.

08:55.577 --> 08:59.955
Maybe he couldn't find you. You don't
spend much time at the house.

09:00.123 --> 09:01.874
I don't have a bed, remember?

09:03.084 --> 09:07.588
-You didn't have a bed in the old house.
-I had a gunshot wound at the old house.

09:07.756 --> 09:11.133
-Yes. You almost died.
-It's not the first time.

09:11.301 --> 09:13.594
[PHONE RINGING]

09:16.097 --> 09:17.681
Who's that?

09:26.316 --> 09:27.900
[DIALING]

09:29.694 --> 09:32.446
[MAN SPEAKING SPANISH
ON OTHER END]

09:34.741 --> 09:37.159
Alarm code from John. He's in trouble.

09:48.838 --> 09:51.298
I need to get some sleep.

09:54.177 --> 09:55.886
And Riley?

09:58.431 --> 10:04.019
I know.

10:14.406 --> 10:16.323
Yeah, right.

10:32.882 --> 10:36.635
Hey. I'll be there in a few minutes.

11:10.211 --> 11:12.338
Please stop doing that.

11:13.256 --> 11:17.760
Look, I got this from my foster parents,
and it's a rape whistle...

11:17.927 --> 11:23.265
-...and it's totally for moments like this.
-Moments like this? Yeah. All right.

11:27.395 --> 11:30.939
When I was a kid,
I lived in Mexico for a year and a half...

11:31.107 --> 11:34.151
...in this little village called Dejalo.

11:35.528 --> 11:40.616
And that's where we're going.

11:41.451 --> 11:44.411
-Thought I'd show you around.
-Wow.

11:45.622 --> 11:49.416
Well, did you run this idea by your mom?
Sometimes I get the impression...

11:49.584 --> 11:51.627
...that she doesn't really like surprises.

11:51.795 --> 11:56.340
-I don't care.
-Did you guys get in a fight last night?

11:57.008 --> 11:58.509
No.

12:00.303 --> 12:05.474
So this is definitely a field trip
and not some revenge fantasy?

12:06.810 --> 12:10.479
If you don't wanna go, cool, but don't
make me feel like I'm kidnapping you.

12:10.647 --> 12:14.233
No, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

12:14.401 --> 12:16.693
You just caught me off guard.

12:16.861 --> 12:20.447
I'm really, really happy that you
wanna show me where you grew up.

12:22.909 --> 12:24.410
Good.

12:26.371 --> 12:28.831
Because I booked
the honeymoon suite.

12:28.998 --> 12:30.916
Wait, what?

12:37.882 --> 12:40.968
It's good, right?
It's nice to get some space.

12:41.678 --> 12:46.473
You and space. The first time we talked,
you were sitting by yourself in the grass.

12:46.641 --> 12:48.142
That was space too.

12:49.185 --> 12:51.353
JOHN:
So it was.

12:51.813 --> 12:53.856
RILEY: You know,
I used to watch you at school.

12:54.399 --> 12:57.985
When the bell would ring
and those narrow hallways would fill up.

12:58.153 --> 13:01.488
It got so loud,
and people would bump into you.

13:01.656 --> 13:05.659
You looked like you could
just jump out the window and run away.

13:06.035 --> 13:08.454
God, you're such a little stalker.

13:08.621 --> 13:13.417
All right, so I get that we ran away
to get some space.

13:14.711 --> 13:16.295
The only shame is...

13:17.922 --> 13:20.924
...we ran all this way,
and there's skulls everywhere.

13:21.092 --> 13:22.843
What, you don't like skulls?

13:23.636 --> 13:24.970
I like other things better.

13:28.183 --> 13:31.894
It's for DÃ­a de los Muertos.
The festival's tonight.

13:32.061 --> 13:33.103
Nice.

13:33.646 --> 13:37.649
Skulls and darkness. How charming.

13:38.818 --> 13:40.986
I'm doing the best I can.

13:46.868 --> 13:49.411
RILEY:
I never wanna leave this room.

13:50.413 --> 13:54.124
-Wait, I think I see the problem.
-Just get in. We don't need bubbles.

13:54.292 --> 13:57.044
There's bubbles to be had,
and I'm gonna have bubbles.

14:03.760 --> 14:05.552
[JACUZZI WHIRRING]

14:06.137 --> 14:08.972
-Not bad, huh?
-You're a total pro.

14:11.601 --> 14:14.186
Wait, you didn't live here
with your mom, did you?

14:14.354 --> 14:15.437
No.

14:15.605 --> 14:19.149
We actually had
a cabana on the beach.

14:20.735 --> 14:24.112
-I think we had very different childhoods.
-It wasn't always good.

14:25.657 --> 14:29.785
Sometimes I wish we'd just stayed here,
away from everybody.

14:32.038 --> 14:35.457
-People suck.
-Not just people.

14:36.751 --> 14:39.628
No, I mean,
when you meet someone...

14:39.796 --> 14:44.341
...you don't really expect
to give a damn about them, right?

14:44.509 --> 14:48.387
Who's got the time?
Life's too short, and people suck.

14:52.100 --> 14:54.560
I don't like getting attached to people.

15:01.609 --> 15:03.443
So...

15:03.903 --> 15:05.904
...why were you living in Mexico?

15:08.866 --> 15:10.951
Oh, you're thinking of a lie or a joke.

15:11.119 --> 15:13.203
-No, I'm not.
-You are. You have a tell.

15:13.371 --> 15:17.124
I just don't wanna sit around
and talk about my messed-up childhood.

15:19.502 --> 15:23.880
-Can't we just we enjoy ourselves?
-Yeah. Fine.

15:24.048 --> 15:27.968
Enjoy yourself. We're not the only couple
that's found themselves...

15:28.136 --> 15:32.014
...in a honeymoon suite and not known
the first thing about each other.

15:40.565 --> 15:42.065
You're right.

15:43.693 --> 15:44.860
People suck.

16:03.838 --> 16:06.506
[JOHN & WAITRESS
SPEAKING SPANISH]

16:10.178 --> 16:12.220
-What was that about?
-Hot sauce.

16:15.266 --> 16:18.060
You know, they do
this killer Thanksgiving buffet here.

16:19.479 --> 16:21.229
I bet.

16:21.606 --> 16:25.025
See? I'm telling you
all sorts of good stuff.

16:26.653 --> 16:28.987
I'm not trying to be your stalker.
I just--

16:29.155 --> 16:32.532
I think this is what we should be doing.
Getting to know each other.

16:32.700 --> 16:34.284
Well, I have a question for you.

16:36.329 --> 16:39.039
You said that I have a tell.

16:39.874 --> 16:41.249
What is it?

16:41.417 --> 16:44.252
Okay, you promise
not to obsess over it or anything?

16:44.420 --> 16:45.962
[CLICK]

16:48.257 --> 16:52.052
What a handsome couple.
And for only $5...

16:52.720 --> 16:54.596
-...a photo memory.
-No, thanks.

16:55.181 --> 16:59.017
See? A beautiful shot.
And it's all digital...

16:59.185 --> 17:03.105
-...which means I can e-mail it to you.
-I think I have something in my teeth.

17:03.272 --> 17:05.691
-Let me take another--
-No, really. That's okay.

17:06.442 --> 17:07.734
Hey, I said it's okay.

17:09.404 --> 17:12.531
Look, man,
why don't I just give you 5 bucks...

17:12.699 --> 17:14.700
...and you'll delete it?
Can we do that?

17:14.867 --> 17:15.867
Gracias.

17:16.119 --> 17:17.536
Thanks.

17:20.581 --> 17:23.667
The young boy and mother
who stayed in Vivian's cabana.

17:24.627 --> 17:26.211
Thanks a lot.

17:27.130 --> 17:28.338
John Connor.

17:29.215 --> 17:30.882
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

17:31.676 --> 17:33.385
You're Sarah Connor's son.

17:36.597 --> 17:38.640
I'll be right back.

17:46.399 --> 17:49.693
I remember
when the Connors left Dejalo.

17:50.027 --> 17:54.990
And I remember the stories
that were told after you were gone.

17:56.743 --> 18:00.036
Man, you really mixed me up
with somebody else. I'm just....

18:00.204 --> 18:03.623
These are pictures you wouldn't want
the authorities to see.

18:04.459 --> 18:06.918
-How much?
-Everything you've got.

18:09.839 --> 18:11.423
JOHN:
Hey. Back off, man.

18:14.135 --> 18:16.094
-We gotta get out of here now. Run.
-No.

18:23.186 --> 18:26.188
[COP SPEAKING SPANISH]

18:39.160 --> 18:40.535
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

18:40.787 --> 18:44.706
Stick to English, kid.
The American accent is killing me.

18:44.957 --> 18:48.585
This is a misunderstanding. That's all.
I'll pay for the camera, okay?

18:48.753 --> 18:51.004
What the hell
were you doing down here anyway?

18:52.340 --> 18:54.382
-We're tourists.
-CancÃºn's no good for you?

18:55.218 --> 18:57.385
CAPTAIN: This is the guy?
COP: Yes, sir.

18:57.553 --> 18:59.846
I was about to take his statement.

19:01.516 --> 19:04.851
A man took a picture of me and my
girlfriend. He wanted us to buy it.

19:05.019 --> 19:06.978
It was crowded.
He dropped his camera.

19:07.146 --> 19:09.898
I was afraid a fight would start,
so we tried to leave.

19:10.066 --> 19:11.858
-How old are you?
-Sixteen.

19:12.026 --> 19:13.401
-You were drinking?
-No.

19:13.569 --> 19:16.655
-You have parents?
-My mother and an uncle.

19:16.823 --> 19:18.740
They know where you are?

19:20.368 --> 19:21.827
No.

19:24.997 --> 19:26.998
CAPTAIN:
I make you a deal.

19:27.166 --> 19:31.086
If they come pick you up,
I let you go with a warning.

19:41.430 --> 19:43.265
DEREK [ON RECORDING]:
Leave a message.

19:46.686 --> 19:48.770
-What was that?
-My uncle's voice mail.

19:48.938 --> 19:50.522
Call your mother.

19:56.279 --> 19:58.363
[DIALING]

19:59.907 --> 20:01.199
SARAH'S VOICE:
Hello?

20:02.785 --> 20:08.081
John? Thank God. Where are you?
I've been going out of my mind.

20:08.791 --> 20:10.250
[TAPPING KEYPAD]

20:11.294 --> 20:13.753
-Did you get through?
SARAH'S VOICE: John, are you there?

20:13.921 --> 20:15.797
Are you in trouble?

20:19.802 --> 20:22.137
She didn't answer.

20:23.723 --> 20:27.142
Put him in holding. In a few hours,
give them another phone call.

20:28.185 --> 20:29.853
And run his name through Interpol.

20:30.354 --> 20:31.897
Yes, sir.

20:34.609 --> 20:36.067
So which name should I run?

20:36.611 --> 20:39.529
The one on your passport
or the real one?

21:06.349 --> 21:11.770
RILEY: Sir. Sir, hello?
Hi. Can you come here, please?

21:20.529 --> 21:22.906
Hi. I need your help, please.

21:23.074 --> 21:27.410
This guy in here is a complete psycho.
He's been trying to make moves on me.

21:27.662 --> 21:29.788
You two came in together.

21:29.956 --> 21:34.042
Sir, do you have children?
Do you have a daughter?

21:34.210 --> 21:37.295
My dad told me to stay away
from this guy. He was totally right.

21:37.463 --> 21:40.674
This guy's a complete freak.
I don't care how much trouble I'm in.

21:40.883 --> 21:44.636
All I wanna do is call home
and tell them where l am.

21:44.971 --> 21:46.513
Please?

21:48.140 --> 21:49.432
Take a step back.

21:49.600 --> 21:52.185
-I'm going to open the door.
-Thank you.

22:01.028 --> 22:02.612
[JOHN SPEAKING SPANISH]

22:02.780 --> 22:04.114
[GUNSHOTS]

22:04.281 --> 22:05.573
[MAN SHOUTING IN SPANISH]

22:05.741 --> 22:07.283
Riley, you need to listen to me.

22:07.451 --> 22:10.704
No matter what happens,
if you see daylight, you run, okay?

22:10.913 --> 22:13.623
-Don't wait for me. Just run.
-John, what are you do--?

22:13.791 --> 22:16.584
If you see daylight, you run.

22:28.305 --> 22:31.099
-Your strategy's changed from last time.
-Has it?

22:31.267 --> 22:34.019
The first time we met,
you tried to kill yourself.

22:34.687 --> 22:37.814
You're right.
This time, I'm gonna kill you.

22:43.571 --> 22:47.115
She hasn't been careful.
She's made mistakes.

22:47.616 --> 22:49.784
Not as many as you, but enough.

22:50.619 --> 22:52.996
Does she have damage to her chip?

22:54.957 --> 22:58.043
-She has damage to her chip.
-How did you find the house?

22:58.502 --> 23:02.672
The boy told me.
The one from the bowling alley.

23:04.967 --> 23:08.678
You should have killed him.
Just like you should have killed yourself.

23:09.555 --> 23:12.140
-I'm not a murderer.
-Who is?

23:33.996 --> 23:36.164
[CAR STARTS]

23:36.749 --> 23:39.209
[SPANISH MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

24:03.484 --> 24:05.026
[CAR STOPS]

24:05.194 --> 24:06.903
[DOOR OPENS]

24:07.071 --> 24:09.864
[FOOTSTEPS WALKING AWAY]

24:12.201 --> 24:13.368
[GUNSHOTS]

24:13.536 --> 24:14.536
[MEN SHOUTING IN SPANISH]

24:14.703 --> 24:16.538
Hey! Hey!

24:16.705 --> 24:18.123
[GUNSHOTS]

24:18.290 --> 24:20.041
[MEN SHOUTING IN SPANISH]

24:20.209 --> 24:21.876
-Hello?
GUY: Now!

24:22.670 --> 24:24.712
Now! Get in!

24:24.880 --> 24:27.549
[GUNFIRE & PEOPLE SHOUTING]

24:27.758 --> 24:29.676
[CAR TIRES SCREECHING]

24:29.969 --> 24:31.636
[GUNFIRE]

24:32.096 --> 24:34.806
[CAR STARTS DRIVING]

24:36.684 --> 24:48.278
[GUNFIRE & PEOPLE SHOUTING]

24:48.946 --> 24:52.490
[ENGINE REWING]

25:02.459 --> 25:03.960
[CAR STOPS]

25:05.045 --> 25:06.963
[CAR DOOR OPENS & CLOSES]

25:07.923 --> 25:09.924
[GUN COCKS]

25:13.262 --> 25:15.346
Sarah Connor? James Ellison.

25:17.766 --> 25:19.893
I need you to come with me.

25:24.440 --> 25:27.483
[PANTING]

25:27.651 --> 25:29.194
[PHONE RINGING]

25:38.078 --> 25:39.954
James Ellison.

25:41.957 --> 25:46.377
Agent Crossman? How you doing?

25:47.713 --> 25:50.965
It's good to hear from you.
What's on your mind?

25:54.803 --> 25:56.512
Mexico?

25:57.848 --> 25:59.599
You don't say.

26:03.145 --> 26:07.982
I suppose they don't have anyone
looking into it over at the bureau.

26:09.235 --> 26:10.652
I know.

26:10.903 --> 26:15.156
Connor case has been cold since '99.
I was just curious.

26:17.910 --> 26:21.412
Sure. E-mail it over and I'll take a look.

26:23.123 --> 26:24.332
[PHONE BLEEPS]

26:24.500 --> 26:25.959
Hold on.

26:33.968 --> 26:37.553
Yeah. Yeah, you're right.
It does look a little bit like him.

26:38.764 --> 26:42.225
John Connor. God rest his soul.

26:42.518 --> 26:47.188
CAPTAIN: You're with the American FBI?
-Yes, sir. That's right.

26:51.235 --> 26:52.860
You have a boy in your custody.

26:53.153 --> 26:56.239
His arrest report
lists an alias of John Connor...

26:56.407 --> 26:58.241
...which matches a fugitive of mine.

26:58.701 --> 27:00.952
The domestic-terrorism case.

27:01.870 --> 27:03.579
You're familiar with the Connors.

27:03.747 --> 27:07.709
It was flagged during processing,
but we dismissed it as a coincidence.

27:08.210 --> 27:10.795
Your fugitive
would be 24 years old by now...

27:10.963 --> 27:12.422
...if he was not already dead.

27:12.798 --> 27:14.173
Look...

27:14.800 --> 27:19.012
...I'd be grateful
for just a visual identification...

27:19.179 --> 27:21.597
...to help bring me some closure.

27:25.436 --> 27:28.563
You have traveled an awful long way
for closure.

27:29.440 --> 27:32.025
If he is who I think he is...

27:32.401 --> 27:35.695
...then I have reason to believe
that your prisoner's in danger.

27:35.904 --> 27:39.282
And, yes, I've come a long way.

27:39.450 --> 27:40.825
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

27:43.454 --> 27:45.580
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

27:46.999 --> 27:48.750
Excuse me.

28:03.640 --> 28:06.184
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

28:07.811 --> 28:10.521
[GUNSHOTS]

28:14.902 --> 28:17.487
[GUNFIRE & MEN SHOUTING]

28:36.173 --> 28:38.132
JOHN:
Daylight. Run!

28:41.303 --> 28:42.845
John! I'm here to help you.

28:45.099 --> 28:48.226
-Oh, my God!
JOHN: The car. Riley!

28:49.103 --> 28:52.146
The car! Riley!
Riley, get in the car! Now!

28:53.816 --> 28:55.900
Now! Get in!

28:59.488 --> 29:01.280
ELLISON:
Get down, get down!

29:12.793 --> 29:15.253
-You okay?
-Yeah. Hey, look at me. Are you okay?

29:15.421 --> 29:16.462
-Yeah, I'm fine.
-Okay.

29:16.630 --> 29:18.673
I'm fine. I'm fine.

29:21.552 --> 29:23.678
JOHN:
Are there any rounds in this thing?

29:27.182 --> 29:28.266
[CLICK]

29:28.642 --> 29:31.102
Look for ammunition.
Look for more ammunition.

29:33.772 --> 29:34.772
[THUMPING]

29:34.940 --> 29:36.691
-What?
-I felt something back here.

29:36.859 --> 29:38.943
Stop the car. Stop the car.

29:47.494 --> 29:48.744
[COCKS GUN]

29:53.459 --> 29:58.129
Sarah Connor? James Ellison.
I need you to come with me.

30:00.340 --> 30:01.883
Mom.

30:05.137 --> 30:06.929
We need to move.

30:25.032 --> 30:28.576
ELLISON: It's a clear shot all the way
up the alley back to the jail.

30:28.827 --> 30:33.080
-No. That's where it'll be waiting.
-Let me do that.

30:34.082 --> 30:36.167
I need to be able to use it.

30:37.419 --> 30:39.420
I should hope so.

30:40.881 --> 30:42.673
Why are you here?

30:45.552 --> 30:47.970
John was flagged in the FBI computer.

30:49.056 --> 30:51.140
Couldn't you just have buried it?

30:54.353 --> 30:56.103
It's been watching me.

30:57.231 --> 30:58.356
"It"?

30:59.566 --> 31:02.318
Out there. It.

31:02.903 --> 31:05.321
And you still came to Mexico?

31:05.656 --> 31:07.323
You could've led it right to John.

31:07.491 --> 31:09.825
-Wasn't me in the trunk.
-What were you gonna do?

31:09.993 --> 31:11.410
Just pop him out of jail?

31:11.578 --> 31:14.956
-Set him free, no questions asked?
ELLISON: Yes, actually.

31:15.123 --> 31:19.544
-That's exactly what I was going to do.
-I have a hard time believing that.

31:22.172 --> 31:23.422
I owed you one.

31:25.467 --> 31:30.221
-The fire. Silberman's cabin.
-Wasn't much.

31:31.306 --> 31:32.848
It was my life.

31:34.977 --> 31:37.019
How you feel about that now?

31:41.024 --> 31:42.775
You have to go.

31:45.821 --> 31:50.283
I promise I'll call you
as soon as we get back to L.A.

31:50.450 --> 31:52.201
-But you have to go.
-John.

31:52.369 --> 31:54.245
Riley, don't.

31:57.624 --> 31:59.333
Go home.

31:59.918 --> 32:02.837
I swear I'll explain everything
when I get there.

32:03.005 --> 32:04.046
Go out the back.

32:04.214 --> 32:07.758
-Run due east. There's a bus route.
-You know what else there is?

32:07.926 --> 32:09.927
A man with a gun who's killing people.

32:10.095 --> 32:13.139
He won't follow you
if you run away from me.

32:13.849 --> 32:16.142
I don't wanna run away from you.

32:19.146 --> 32:20.187
Get her out of here.

32:29.406 --> 32:31.240
I need your phone.

32:31.742 --> 32:35.661
ELLISON: Have a plan?
-Got a weapon.

32:36.204 --> 32:37.830
Cameron.

32:38.373 --> 32:40.333
The girl from the bank vault?

32:45.714 --> 32:47.089
DEREK [ON PHONE]:
Yeah?

32:49.426 --> 32:52.136
-I need you and Cameron.
-John's with you?

32:52.304 --> 32:54.597
-We're here already. We're at the jail.
-What?

33:09.613 --> 33:13.949
-Cromartie's here.
-Then we should stay under cover.

33:16.703 --> 33:17.912
Hey.

33:19.998 --> 33:21.540
Metal.

33:33.428 --> 33:36.180
I'm looking for John Baum.
Where is he?

33:36.348 --> 33:37.348
[CAPTAIN SPEAKS SPANISH]

33:37.516 --> 33:39.725
-We gotta get out of here.
-We gotta find John.

33:39.893 --> 33:41.977
We're no good to him dead.

33:44.272 --> 33:46.774
I can't let anything happen to him.

33:56.201 --> 33:59.537
-Escaped or dead?
-Escaped.

33:59.996 --> 34:04.709
-A little help?
-Don't worry. It won't be back.

34:04.876 --> 34:07.628
SeÃ±or, please!

34:07.796 --> 34:09.046
[PHONE RINGING]

34:12.634 --> 34:14.135
Yeah?

34:15.178 --> 34:17.054
SARAH:
John and I are in trouble. I need you--

34:17.222 --> 34:19.849
John's with you? We're here already.

34:20.016 --> 34:22.810
-We're at the jail.
-What?

34:22.978 --> 34:27.231
Wait, wait, wait, Sarah.
Then where the hell's Cromartie?

34:31.486 --> 34:35.448
CAPTAIN: I'm sorry, seÃ±or.
I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

34:35.615 --> 34:38.033
I'm gonna need to see John Connor.

34:40.036 --> 34:43.497
[GUNSHOTS]

35:10.192 --> 35:11.358
[GUNSHOT]

35:15.655 --> 35:18.449
COP:
Help! Help me!

35:25.874 --> 35:28.709
-I'm looking for John Connor.
-He's gone.

35:29.878 --> 35:32.213
Are there any other exits?

35:32.881 --> 35:34.465
No.

35:53.693 --> 35:56.237
JOHN: The car! Riley!
Riley, get in the car! Now!

37:42.844 --> 37:45.262
Have you come to repent?

37:45.680 --> 37:48.015
I'm looking for John Connor.

37:48.683 --> 37:52.811
All things are possible
to him who believes.

39:43.423 --> 39:46.800
We'll attract less attention
if we don't travel together.

39:47.969 --> 39:49.887
You want me to leave.

39:51.514 --> 39:54.600
-What's next?
-We'll come back down here...

39:56.311 --> 39:59.146
...and bring something with us
to destroy it.

40:01.316 --> 40:06.195
ELLISON: His name's gonna be on an alert.
-He's got other names.

40:07.489 --> 40:09.114
Then what?

40:09.324 --> 40:11.408
There is no "then what."

40:11.785 --> 40:13.160
Pretend I died again.

40:14.829 --> 40:18.373
I lost a lot
when you died the first time.

40:18.541 --> 40:20.793
My marriage. My career.

40:21.795 --> 40:23.837
That's a lot to you?

40:27.842 --> 40:30.177
I suppose many people
lost those things.

40:35.850 --> 40:37.643
You want answers.

40:38.061 --> 40:41.355
I just wanna know my role
in all of this.

40:41.523 --> 40:43.065
What happens after this?

40:43.691 --> 40:45.359
This is it.

40:47.028 --> 40:49.696
There's nothing else
behind the curtain.

40:50.532 --> 40:53.367
This is what I do. It's all I do.

40:53.993 --> 40:56.537
You already know why I do it.

40:58.456 --> 41:00.874
I'm sorry for what you lost...

41:01.709 --> 41:04.336
...but I can't help you
get any of it back.

41:13.346 --> 41:15.180
Can I have the chip?

41:38.621 --> 41:46.128
Ah!

42:01.603 --> 42:03.228
[SARAH SOBBING]
